  "text": "Spleen cell suspensions were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] . Peritoneal macrophage suspensions were prepared according to a previously described procedure [CITATION_2] . Macrophages were confirmed to constitute over 95% of the adherent viable cells by treatment with esterase and Giemsa staining. The cell density was adjusted to 1.0 × 10 6 /ml and cells were placed into wells of a 24-well flat-bottom plate (Sarstedt Inc., Newton, NC, USA). Cells were cultured at 37°C in a humidified incubator Table 1 6 with an atmosphere of 5% CO2.",
